THE only thing standing between Lungile Gongqa and his Old Mutual Two Oceans ultra marathon title defence is himself. Gongqa is not worried about anyone, not even the strong competition from neighbouring countries Lesotho and Zimbabwe. The Nedbank running club athlete is confident that he will be able to defend his title in the gruelling 56km race in Cape Town on Easter Saturday. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvF7M3cBQwP-K19sLLWh8DcnqChi8QhFmc3u5vmiHOFaBTmOeoa-djwBRx2coYIjQdfs790n1bpvEeWYvkFVax2_5B3QgWf0ZgL72A5FdersBUaBEV-XojIBXCziJ5mTKBfA6nrA9wESHpZ0OC0zMcxyf1Ht9ldG1_FnEIsHrbOwvMUAo2QCNuiESPs0FG2Sj5wHCCkb1rwTbDREzXT_xyy0Ecaf7W9HpmjcIH6uZ-7MfWWbhJfrgMgdZHr1vzDqllA8gxW1PBqn864N6Wg\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzDgIncwC7G6aEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
